Beijing National Stadium | The opening ceremony gets underway, with 3,000 performers featuring in the 100-minute celebration  The Bird's Nest | Beijing's iconic stadium also played host to the Summer Olympics in 2008  Bing Dwen Dwen | One of the Winter Olympics mascots waves to the crowd  Official welcome | IOC President Thomas Bach greets the crowd alongside Chinese President Xi Jinping  National pride | The host country's flag is raised to signal the ceremony's beginning  Vladimir Putin | The Russian President's presence has caused headlines amid rising tensions with Ukraine  Flag bearers | Ukrainian athletes parade in front of a crowd of spectators, one of which is Putin  Ice dancers | Performers dressed as ice hockey players during the opening ceremony  Sport without politics? | The USA contingent enters the stadium, despite US government officials boycotting the Games in light of China's human rights record  Beijing lights | Performers create a flower display with LED lights  Host parade | China's athletes enter the stadium last to loud cheers from the crowd  Peace speech | IOC President Thomas Bach said the Olympics stood for a world with "no discrimination whatsoever" and urged people to "give peace a chance."  Let the Games begin | Fireworks signal the end of the opening ceremony